# TaskFlow: Mobile & Web Walkthrough

## 1. Web App Enhancements

The existing `taskflow-app` React frontend was completely transformed to integrate real backend logic while preserving its sophisticated UI.

### Authentication Flow
- **[AuthContext.jsx](file:///d:/Developments/College%20Project/taskflow-app/src/context/AuthContext.jsx)**: Handles session persistence via `localStorage`, automatically checking the `/auth/me` endpoint on initialization.
- **Glassmorphism UI**: Designed a stunning [LoginPage.jsx](file:///d:/Developments/College%20Project/taskflow-app/src/pages/LoginPage.jsx), [RegisterPage.jsx](file:///d:/Developments/College%20Project/taskflow-app/src/pages/RegisterPage.jsx), and [ForgotPasswordPage.jsx](file:///d:/Developments/College%20Project/taskflow-app/src/pages/ForgotPasswordPage.jsx) featuring dynamic accent glows based on the system color tokens.
- **OTP Integration**: Built a sleek 6-digit auto-advancing input component for the [ForgotPasswordPage](file:///d:/Developments/College%20Project/taskflow-app/src/pages/ForgotPasswordPage.jsx#70-240), hooked directly to the Mailtrap OTP backend.

### Real-Time Data Layer
- **[DataContext.jsx](file:///d:/Developments/College%20Project/taskflow-app/src/context/DataContext.jsx)**: The core data layer powering the web app. It fetches initial lists (Tasks, Events, Team, Notifications) using custom API wrappers (`src/api/*`).
- **Socket.IO Sync**: Automatically establishes a WebSocket connection with the backend (`API_URL`), forwarding the authentication JWT. Real-time updates push new elements directly into the React state seamlessly, avoiding re-fetching.
- **Dynamic Bindings**: [Dashboard.jsx](file:///d:/Developments/College%20Project/taskflow-app/src/components/Dashboard.jsx), [Tasks.jsx](file:///d:/Developments/College%20Project/taskflow-app/src/components/Tasks.jsx), [Team.jsx](file:///d:/Developments/College%20Project/taskflow-app/src/components/Team.jsx) now pull directly from React Context rather than dummy files. 
    - The delegation chain in [Team.jsx](file:///d:/Developments/College%20Project/taskflow-app/src/components/Team.jsx) dynamically tracks the specific `parent_task_id` hierarchies.
    - Notification panels show real unread counts and instantly push new alerts (via WebSocket).
- **Responsive Navigation**: Overhauled [global.css](file:///d:/Developments/College%20Project/taskflow-app/src/styles/global.css) with mobile breakpoints. Features grid reflows to 1 or 2 columns and hides sidebar navigation gracefully under `@media (max-width: 768px)`.

---

## 2. React Native (Expo) Mobile App

Built entirely new inside `taskflow-mobile/`, sharing the exact visual identity as the web application but using native primitives.

### Scaffolding
- Hand-authored standard configs ([package.json](file:///d:/Developments/College%20Project/taskflow-app/package.json), [app.json](file:///d:/Developments/College%20Project/taskflow-mobile/app.json), [babel.config.js](file:///d:/Developments/College%20Project/taskflow-mobile/babel.config.js)) to fix Expo initialization constraints for absolute compatibility with React Navigation v6, enabling a flawless dark UI out of the box.
- Included `@react-navigation/bottom-tabs` for seamless swiping and persistent memory contexts.

### Contexts & API
- **Seamless Porting**: Migrated web [AuthContext.jsx](file:///d:/Developments/College%20Project/taskflow-app/src/context/AuthContext.jsx) and [DataContext.jsx](file:///d:/Developments/College%20Project/taskflow-app/src/context/DataContext.jsx) into React Native by switching `fetch` wrappers to use `@react-native-async-storage/async-storage`.
- **API Auto-Refresh**: Customized [client.js](file:///d:/Developments/College%20Project/taskflow-app/src/api/client.js) with retry-logic. When encountering customized 401 Unauthenticated API requests, it retrieves the fallback refresh ticket and dispatches a JSON `POST /auth/refresh` — exploiting the previous backend update designed precisely to bypass restrictive HTTP-only cookie environments. 
- **Socket.IO Mobile Client**: Directly initializes real-time capabilities so task creation on the mobile instantly materializes on the user’s web browser, and vice versa.

### Native Screens
- **Auth Stack**: [LoginScreen](file:///d:/Developments/College%20Project/taskflow-mobile/src/screens/LoginScreen.js#6-51) and [RegisterScreen](file:///d:/Developments/College%20Project/taskflow-mobile/src/screens/RegisterScreen.js#6-54) wrap `TextInput` and styled `TouchableOpacity` elements within custom UI cards that feel just like the web variant, retaining the signature `#060B12` backgrounds.
- **Tab Navigation**: [DashboardScreen](file:///d:/Developments/College%20Project/taskflow-mobile/src/screens/DashboardScreen.js#13-119), [TasksScreen](file:///d:/Developments/College%20Project/taskflow-mobile/src/screens/TasksScreen.js#12-122), [TeamScreen](file:///d:/Developments/College%20Project/taskflow-mobile/src/screens/TeamScreen.js#6-49), [CalendarScreen](file:///d:/Developments/College%20Project/taskflow-mobile/src/screens/CalendarScreen.js#9-118) replicate the layout natively using standard native Flexbox logic and robust `FlatList` mechanisms.
- **Calendars**: Integrated `react-native-calendars` marking days accurately based on the live response fed via Context.

---

## 3. Backend & Security Architecture Fixes
- Added logic enabling cross-device sessions since `httpOnly` secure tokens do not seamlessly interact with mobile operating systems.
- Appended [app.js](file:///d:/Developments/College%20Project/taskflow-backend/src/app.js) with exact Localhost/LAN domains typical of an active Expo development server instance.

Everything correctly falls into place. The web experience shines with the newly integrated data contexts, and the mobile Expo layout mirrors the functionality beautifully native on-device natively.
